## Never do

- `unsafe` without SAFETY comment and UNSAFE_AUDIT entry
- Capability operations without Kani harness
- Kernel IPC without threat node
- `unwrap()` in kernel without PANIC-OK
- Skip ADR on architectural tradeoffs
- Batch unrelated subsystems in one commit
- Claim tier A/B is "proven correct"
- Shrink Kani bounds to pass proofs
- Ambient authority in any server
- Copy Linux/Windows semantics without ADR justification

